- ts: 2026-04-29T16:50:22Z
  event: clarify_critic
  feature: decide-and-document-post-47-policy-settings-must-escalation-tone-regression
  findings:
    - "The HIGH intent-clarity rating leans on 'deliverable is short written policy entries answering both', but OQ3 is framed as a conditional rule ('keep or normalize back and re-observe'), and the ticket does not say how to weight #85's empirical input against Anthropic's two contradictory docs."
    - "Scope is rated HIGH but the ticket embeds an unresolved target-location decision (CLAUDE.md vs ~/.claude/rules/cortex-*.md if cortex-deploys-only-rules conventions apply) that the assessment dismisses as 'part of the policy decision itself' — the orchestrator's characterization, not the ticket's."
    - "Requirements alignment cites the auto-memory entry 'Cortex is rules-only, never ships global CLAUDE.md' as evidence the user's personal ~/.claude/CLAUDE.md is ruled out, but that is out-of-source context. The ticket itself names CLAUDE.md without distinguishing repo-CLAUDE.md from global-CLAUDE.md."
    - "Requirements alignment asserts alignment with project.md, but the ticket body does not reference project.md and the assessment does not quote what in project.md actually applies to a prompt-engineering-policy decision."
    - "Complexity is rated 'simple' on 'mechanical writing once decisions are made', which brackets out the actual judgment work — squaring two contradictory upstream sources via #85 evidence is precisely a design-trade-off judgment task, not mechanical."
    - "Criticality is rated medium, but the entries land in CLAUDE.md or ~/.claude/rules/cortex-*.md — both loaded on every session and propagating into every future skill-authoring decision. The 'high default for shared agentic-layer infrastructure' rule was waved off without source-grounded reasoning."
  dispositions:
    apply: 5
    dismiss: 1
    ask: 0
  applied_fixes:
    - "Acknowledged target-file routing (repo CLAUDE.md vs ~/.claude/rules/cortex-*.md) as an Open Question for Research, dependent on each policy's deployment scope; scope rating stays HIGH because the routing is bounded by the in-repo cortex deployment model from #120/#121."
    - "Reframed requirements-alignment evidence to cite the cortex-deployment-only-rules convention as established by completed tickets #120/#121 (in-repo, verifiable), not auto-memory."
    - "Softened project.md alignment statement to 'no conflicts detected; project.md is silent on prompt-engineering-policy specifics, so alignment is by absence-of-conflict rather than affirmative endorsement'."
    - "Escalated complexity from 'simple' to 'complex' — the OQ3 decision is a judgment call requiring synthesis of #85 audit findings with Anthropic's two contradictory upstream guidance docs."
    - "Escalated criticality from 'medium' to 'high' — entries shape future skill-authoring decisions across the agentic layer; rubric default for shared agentic-layer infrastructure is high."
  dismissals:
    - finding_index: 0
      rationale: "Intent clarity is about whether the goal is unambiguous, not whether the decision is easy. The intent (decide and document the OQ3 reconciliation, decide and document OQ6) is clearly stated. The difficulty of arriving at the decision is a research/spec-phase concern, not an intent-clarity concern."
  status: ok
